definition.value: An amino trisaccharide consisting of beta-D-glucopyranuronic acid, 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranose and beta-D-glucopyranuronic acid residues joined in sequence by (1->4) glycosidic bonds.
A disaccharide phosphate consisting of 6-phospho-alpha-D-mannopyranose and D-mannopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
A disaccharide that is D-mannitol in which the hydroxy group at position 3 has been converted into the corresponding alpha-L-fucoside.
An L-galactofuranose that has alpha- configuration at the anomeric centre.
An alpha-D-Glcp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Glcp-(1->4)]-D-Glcp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has alpha- configuration.
A 1-O-(D-glucosyl)glycerol in which the D-glucosyl moiety has beta configuration at the anomeric centre.
A disaccharide that is D-galactopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 has been converted into the corresponding alpha-D-glucopyranosyl derivative.
